      "role": "radio_relic_primary",
      "description": "VLA 1.4 GHz detection of the radio relic 'the Bullet' — a diffuse radio structure at the bow shock front. Synchrotron radiation from electrons accelerated at the Mach~3 shock. In BEC model: the bow shock is the leading edge of the BEC interference wavefront propagating through the medium. The radio relic IS the electromagnetic signature of the medium boundary. Spectral index α ~ -1.0 (steep, aged electrons).",
      "mode": "tap_adql",
      "endpoint": "https://tapvizier.cds.unistra.fr/TAPVizieR/tap",
