      "waveband": "submm_sz",
      "role": "sz_pressure_map",
      "description": "Planck all-sky SZ Compton y-parameter map at the Bullet Cluster position. Compton y = ∫ (kT_e/m_e c²) n_e dl — traces the integrated electron pressure along the line of sight. Co-located with X-ray gas peak (both trace pressure). Should be at σ=½ (causality) — gas is the baryonic, causal component. In BEC model: gas occupies the σ=½ region (the | crossing) while the BEC interference peaks (σ=1) contain no gas.",
      "mode": "fits",
