      "name": "twomass_infrared",
      "telescope": "2MASS",
      "instrument": "2MASS J + H + Ks",
      "waveband": "nearir",
      "role": "stellar_mass_tracer",
      "description": "2MASS infrared catalog of stellar sources in the Bullet Cluster field. Near-infrared is the best tracer of stellar mass (minimizes dust, maximizes M/L ratio stability). Stellar mass distribution traces the 'leaves' — the visible matter in the bowl. Combined with lensing: stellar mass tracks DM offset (Harvey 2015). In BEC model: stars are leaves on the water. Of course they track the bowl — they are IN the medium.",
