  "evaluation": {
    "fn": "σ_face_bullet_alldata_dispatch",
    "methodology": "I am measuring the ratio of signal to ambient background per waveband across all telescopes that resolved the Bullet Cluster. X-ray: J = counts / background → σ=½ expected at gas peak (baryonic causality). Lensing: J = κ / κ_ambient → σ=1 expected at mass peaks (Yang-Mills, BEC interference). Radio/SZ: J = flux / rms → σ=½ expected co-located with gas. Gamma null: J = flux_UL / CDM_predicted → J < 1 expected everywhere (no particles to annihilate). The shape has inside and outside. Gas is inside (causality, σ=½). The lensing peaks are the shape itself (σ=1). They are not stuffed with particles — they ARE the geometry.",

    "prediction": "SMMIP BEC interference model predictions (zero free parameters): (1) Lensing peaks → J = κ/κ_ambient > 1/d* = 4.07 → σ=1 (Yang-Mills). (2) Gas peak (X-ray, SZ) → J ≈ 1 → σ=½ (causality). (3) Gamma null (Fermi, HESS) → J < d* → σ=∞ (below causal floor, no particle content). (4) BEC fringe test: σ-face profile between the two lensing peaks shows ALTERNATING σ=1/σ=½ fringes at λ_fringe ≈ 1.5 arcmin. CDM predicts monotone σ=1 blob, no alternation. (5) Stellar mass (2MASS, HST) → σ=½ (leaves on the water — stellar matter in causality regime, not in the shape itself).",

